<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-550-096  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 550 096.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 15 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Practical Peripherals sold to Hayes. (Hayes MicrocomputerProducts)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Practical Peripherals Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)Hayes Microcomputer Products Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     AcquisitionModemsManufacturers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PRACTICAL PERIPHERALS SOLD TO HAYES WESTLAKE VILLAGE, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A.,andO;1989 AUG 8 (NB) -- Practical Peripherals has been sold to Hayes MicrocomputerProducts of Atlanta.andP;  Both companies are makers of modem devices.andP;  PracticalPeripherals will continue to operate as a wholly- owned subsidiary of Hayesand its current management will remain in place.andP;  Practical Peripherals willbe known by its own name as a separate corporation with &quot;A Hayes Company&quot;added.andP;  The company will remain in its California location and continueproduct development activities at that location.andP;  Financial terms of thisagreement are being kept confidential.andP;  As part of the acquisition, Hayes andPractical Peripherals have settled litigation pertaining to the Modem withImproved Escape Sequence patent issued to Hayes in 1985.andP;  The acquisition ofPractical Peripherals gives Hayes an entre into the lower-end, pricesensitive part of the modem market.andP;  (Janet Endrijonas/19890811/PressContact: Debbie Lacy, Lloyd andamp; Clark Marketing andCommunications/818-990-1235)</TEXT></DOC>